Package frc.robot.commands

Contains all the commands that can be used to control the robot and its functions, including driving and running all subsystems such as indexing and shooting. Note about the commands, all of the print statements have been commented out, they're okay to have but we had to disable them during competition because of the performance drop we were experience on the Driver Station just to see if it would help.

For the record, the issue was actually having ShuffleBoard running in the background, for some reason it was heavily using the Driver Station's CPU and was leading to a lot of latency between the laptop and FMS so be careful when using it. Likewise, print statements can also cause issues so be careful when printing a ton of data too.

Please note that I will NOT be going over the Command-based programming paradigm here in documentation, FRC has some pretty extensive docs that cover this. However, I will be leaving small notes on a few methods just to denote why certain things are set the way they are.

Also note that I'm 99% sure I did the programming for the Command-based structure super inefficiently and that there's a far easier way to have basic controls be implemented. A lot of these are mostly just toggles to move a subsystem one direction or another, or to set specific speeds or modes. I have a feeling this could possibly be fixed via suppliers, whether they be in the form of doubles or booleans or at least have sort of state management system so that we don't end up with 26 different commands that all accomplish similar things, but it's definitely something to keep in mind for the future.

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArcadeDriveCmd
    ArcadeDriveCmd class that allows for the robot to drive in arcade drive
    AutoShootCmd
    AutoShootCmd class that allows for us to automatically index and shoot the ball when the shooting trigger is pressed.
    CycleCameraModeCmd
    CycleCameraModeCmd class that allows for the user to cycle between the different streaming modes of the Limelight.
    DropPivotCmd
    DropPivotCmd class that drops the Pickup mechanism towards the front of the robot
    EmptyCommand
    EmptyCommand class that is...
    FastPickupCmd
    FastPickupCmd class that runs the pickup at full speed to pick up power cells from the field.
    IndexCmd
    IndexCmd class that allows for power cells to be indexed and moved from the pickup to the shooter.
    PickupCmd
    PickupCmd class that runs the pickup at normal speed to pick up power cells from the field
    RaisePivotCmd
    RasiePivotCmd class that raises the Pickup mechanism back within the frame perimeter of the robot.
    ResetDTPoseCmd
    ResetDTPoseCmd class that resets the odometry of the DriveTrain to aid in trajectory following
    ReverseDTCmd
    ReverseDTCmd class that reverses the entire drivetrain of the robot to now drive backwards both in autonomous and in normal driving as well, so that the back becomes the front and the front becomes the back
    ReverseIndexerCmd
    ReverseIndexerCmd class that spins the indexer in the opposite direction in the case of needing to eject a ball
    ReversePickupCmd
    ReversePickupCmd class that spins the pickup in the opposite direction in the case of needing to eject a ball
    ReverseShootCmd
    ReverseShootCmd class that spins the shooter in the opposite direction in the case of needing to eject a ball, although it is unlikely that this will actually help unlike ReverseIndexerCmd or ReversePickupCmd.
    RunClimberCmd
    RunClimberCmd class that runs the climber according to its current specified speed within Climber
    RunLeftClimberCmd
    RunLeftClimberCmd class that was supposed to run the left climber independently from the right one, but all the code is commented out so it does nothing.
    RunRightClimberCmd
    RunRightClimberCmd that was supposed to run the right climber independently from the left one, but all the code is commented out so it does nothing.
    SetHighGoalCmd
    SetHighGoalCmd class that sets the shooter to its "High Goal" speed and threshold
    SetLowGoalCmd
    SetLowGoalCmd class that sets the shooter to its "Low Goal" speed and threshold
    SetPipelineCmd
    SetPipelineCmd class that allows for the user to cycle between the different pipelines of the Limelight.
    SetToClimbSpeedCmd
    SetToClimbSpeedCmd class that sets the climber speed for climbing the robot
    SetToExtendSpeedCmd
    SetToExtendSpeedCmd class that sets the climber speed for extending them upwards
    ShootCmd
    ShootCmd class that runs the shooter mechanism independently from all other subsystems
    SubsystemSpeedSetter
    SubsystemSpeedSetting class that allows for us to manually set the speeds of each individual subsystem on the fly.
    TargetBallCmd
    TargetBallCmd class that targets power cells on the field using the Limelight and computer vision.
    TurnToAngleCommand
    TurnToAngleCommand class that turns the robot to a given heading for the autonomous period.
